{"lemma":"جَمَلٌ","slug":"جَمَلٌ","root":"ج.م.ل","root_slug":"ج-م-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-م-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جَمَل","root":"جمل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6345"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sum up, to summarize"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَمَلَ (jamala) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of جُمْلَة (jumla)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be beautiful, to be pretty, to be graceful"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be handsome, to be comely"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be appropriate, to be proper, to be suitable"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make beautiful, to beautify, to embellish, to adorn"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"male camel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ellipsis of جَمَل الْيَهُود (jamal al-yahūd, “chameleon; mantis”)","tags":["abbreviation","alt-of","ellipsis"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-West Semitic *gamal-."},"ipa":["/d͡ʒu.mal/","/d͡ʒa.mal/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6345","headword_ar":"جَمَلٌ","root":"jml","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamolN","text_ar":"جَمْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which latter is so rare that it is said by some to be used only in poetry, in cases of necessity, (MF,) but it is a correct dial. var., (TA,) a word of well-known meaning; (K;) i. e., ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A he-camel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but commonly applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a generic term; in like manner as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAmilN","text_ar":"جَامِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to the males and the females; but properly,] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibil","text_ar":"اـِبِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mate of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqap","text_ar":"نَاقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Fr, S, Mgh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among camels, corresponding to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among us;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"corresponding to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroA^apN","text_ar":"مَرْاَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakorN","text_ar":"بَكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulaAmN","text_ar":"غُلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakorapN","text_ar":"بَكْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAriyapN","text_ar":"جَارِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sh, TA;) [in general] peculiarly applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) exceptionally to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aribotu labana jamaliY","text_ar":"شَرِبْتُ لَبَنَ جَمَلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I drank the milk of my she-camel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but ISd doubts the correctness of this: (TA:) [as corresponding to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"among us, it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a full-grown hecamel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaAEK","text_ar":"رَبَاعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one in his seventh year"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, ISd, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja*aEN","text_ar":"جَذَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one in his fifth year"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (ISd, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAzilN","text_ar":"بَازِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one in his ninth year"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (ISd, Mgh, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaniY~N","text_ar":"ثَنِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one in his sixth year"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (ISd, K:) or, accord. to Z,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that has covered:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiyrN","text_ar":"بَعِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakorN","text_ar":"بَكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEuwdN","text_ar":"قَعُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomaAlN","text_ar":"اَجْمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) which may be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamolN","text_ar":"جَمْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomulN","text_ar":"اَجْمُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jimaAlN","text_ar":"جِمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jumolN","text_ar":"جُمْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jimaAlapN","text_ar":"جِمَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K) and [quasi-pl. n.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jumaAlapN","text_ar":"جُمَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAlapN","text_ar":"جَمَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAmilN","text_ar":"جَامِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which last is disallowed by some, as will be seen below, (TA,) and [pl. pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jimaAlaAtN","text_ar":"جِمَالَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) which is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jimaAlN","text_ar":"جِمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) or it may be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jimaAlapN","text_ar":"جِمَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jumaAlaAtN","text_ar":"جُمَالَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see also voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jum~alN","text_ar":"جُمَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAlaAtN","text_ar":"جَمَالَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAy^ilu","text_ar":"جَمَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jmAlp","text_ar":"جمالة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jimAl","text_ar":"جِمال"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ham p. 527,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajaAmilu","text_ar":"اَجَامِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) One says of camels, when they are males, without any female among them,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi jimaAlapu baniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ جِمَالَةُ بَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These are the hecamels of the sons of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (ISk, S. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jumaAlapN","text_ar":"جُمَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And they said also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jimaAlaAni","text_ar":"جِمَالَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two herds of camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus forming a dual from the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jimaAlN","text_ar":"جِمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], like as they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liqaAHaAni","text_ar":"لِقَاحَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISd, in TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayolN","text_ar":"خَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAA@sotatara mano qaAda Aljamala","text_ar":"مَاا@سْتَتَرَ مَنْ قَادَ الجَمَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He does not conceal himself who leads the he-camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And in another prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~axa*a All~ayola jamalFA","text_ar":"اِتَّخَذَ اللَّيْلَ جَمَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He journeyed all the night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA. [See also Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 230.]) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljamalu","text_ar":"الجَمَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain fish"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thirty cubits in length:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamalu","text_ar":"جَمَلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaHori","text_ar":"البَحْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a very great fish, also called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAl","text_ar":"بَال"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the whale,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thirty cubits in length:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to some, this, (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamalu AlmaA='i","text_ar":"جَمَلُ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kawosaj","text_ar":"كَوْسَج"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kubaE","text_ar":"كُبَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luxom","text_ar":"لُخْم"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"xiphias,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sword-fish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which passes by nothing without cutting it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [In the present day,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamalu AlbaHori","text_ar":"جَمَلُ البَحْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pelican."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayonu Aljamali","text_ar":"عَيْنُ الجَمَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the dial. of Egypt,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aAh bal~uwT","text_ar":"الشَّاه بَلُّوط"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The chestnut"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamalN","text_ar":"جَمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)  A woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ax*","text_ar":"اخذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qyd","text_ar":"قيد"},{"kind":"text","text":". See 2 in each of those arts.) ―         -b5-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Palm-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) as being likened to the he-camel in respect of their tallness and their bigness and their produce: in some of the copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aHolu","text_ar":"النَّحْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~axolu","text_ar":"النَّخْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jum~alN","text_ar":"جُمَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","MF","TA","S","ISd","Mgh","Msb","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}